Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of the Breadth First Search algorithm, which is a fundamental graph traversal algorithm and falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper specifically mentions social networks in the title and discusses the implications of the results for graph processing in distributed computing environments, which are relevant to the domain of social and information networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses parallel implementations of the BFS algorithm and the use of partitioning to reduce message overhead, which are relevant to the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the implications of the results for graph processing in distributed computing environments, which are relevant to the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of partitioning to reduce message overhead in parallel implementations of the BFS algorithm, which falls under the domain of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing.
